In this experiment, you will:

Install and set up Slack

Create a workspace in Slack

Create a channel (example: #jenkins-alerts)

Install the Slack app in Jenkins

Generate a Slack Webhook / Token

Configure Jenkins to send build notifications to Slack

This is used in CI/CD pipelines so your team receives a message when:

Build succeeds

Build fails

Build starts

Build finishes

